The article discusses the President and First Lady's call to action on college opportunity. They are partnering with colleges, universities, business leaders, nonprofits, and others to support more college opportunities for students across the country. Over 100 new commitments have been made to expand college opportunity, including connecting more low-income students to the right college, increasing the pool of students preparing for college through early interventions, leveling the playing field in college advising and test preparation, and strengthening remediation to help academically underprepared students. The article also highlights the importance of improving college opportunity for increasing economic mobility and growing the economy. The Department of Education is also taking actions to support low-income students, such as leveraging work-study jobs for mentoring and building the evidence base for early intervention programs.